                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13592213" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 4 Mar 2013 14:02:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We should build a notice into the cli since this keeps coming up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13592230" author="karpa13a" created="Mon, 4 Mar 2013 14:23:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;created CF with cqlsh -3 not visible(and unusable) in thrift api (phpcassa and cassandra-cli)&lt;br/&gt;
but CF created in phpcassa/cassandra-cli visible and accessible in cqlsh -3 and phpcassa/cassandra-cli&lt;br/&gt;
C* 1.2.2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;related to this ticket?&lt;br/&gt;
or this is feature?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13592232" author="iamaleksey" created="Mon, 4 Mar 2013 14:26:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is the intended behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13592999" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 5 Mar 2013 03:12:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13593006" author="iamaleksey" created="Tue, 5 Mar 2013 03:24:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13593016" author="karpa13a" created="Tue, 5 Mar 2013 03:30:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;may be add this warning after &apos;create column family ...&apos; statement in cqlsh -3 too?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13593030" author="jayadevan.maymala@ibsplc.com" created="Tue, 5 Mar 2013 03:37:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am a newcomer in the world of NoSQL databases. Whether we create a column family using cli or a table using cqlsh, aren&apos;t the same things happening under the covers? So why is an object created using one interface not visible in the other?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13593033" author="iamaleksey" created="Tue, 5 Mar 2013 03:42:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jayadevan.maymala%40ibsplc.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jayadevan.maymala@ibsplc.com&quot;&gt;jayadevan.maymala@ibsplc.com&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4377&quot; title=&quot;CQL3 column value validation bug&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4377&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4377&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13593042" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 5 Mar 2013 03:52:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hang on, printing to stdout means you can no longer round-trip a &apos;show schema&apos; through a file.  stderr seems a better choice.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13593050" author="iamaleksey" created="Tue, 5 Mar 2013 04:04:34 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hang on, printing to stdout means you can no longer round-trip a &apos;show schema&apos; through a file. stderr seems a better choice.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is good - this way when schema fails to replay they&apos;ll definitely notice the warning.&lt;br/&gt;
Just kidding - fixed in b1abbf2d05d8cdf46c08a7a6e5289c9ade98dd3b. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
